  "text": "Thermococcus litoralis DSM 5473 was maintained in complex medium (CM) under strictly anaerobic conditions at 85°C [CITATION_1] . For the gene expression experiments, cells were grown in defined medium (D), in D supplemented with 0. E. coli XL1-Blue MRF' and E. coli BL21(DE3) CodonPlus-RIL (Stratagene) cells were used for cloning and protein overexpression, respectively. E. coli strains were cultivated in Luria-Bertani medium [33] at 37°C, antibiotics were used at the following concentrations (μg·ml -1 ): ampicillin (100), kanamycin (50) , and tetracycline [CITATION_2] .",
